[i]“Memories faded as emotions built;
 as the Poison-Tongued saw a ripe treat.
Grasping out and holding tight;
 memories dissolved overnight”
—[/i]The Koiosode[i][/i]

[i]The call of the Dead was loud and frightful;
 beckoning the nyxborn to delve deeper.
For twice memories lost a new one gained;
 but were these his or from a fable never told?”
—[/i]The Koiosode[i][/i]

[i]The gods stayed silent as the moments swayed;
 as unlikely as it was, peace was had.
The two were able to sit in each other's silence;
 remembering the memories of their past.”
—[/i]The Koiosode[i][/i]
